## Installation
npm install zca-js

## API: loginQR

### Description
Authenticate (login) a Zalo personal account using QR Code.

This API initializes a login session and generates a QR code that must be scanned using the Zalo mobile app.  
After successful scan, the system returns an authenticated API instance used for all further interactions.

---

### Method (zca-js)
zalo.loginQR(options)

---

### Parameters

- userAgent: string (optional)  
  → Custom user agent for the login session

- qrPath: string (optional)  
  → File path to save QR code image  
  → Default: ./qr.png

---

### Example

```ts
import { Zalo } from "zca-js";

const zalo = new Zalo({
    selfListen: false,
    checkUpdate: true,
    logging: true
});

const api = await zalo.loginQR({
    userAgent: "",
    qrPath: "./qr.png"
});

api.listener.start();
```

## API: getQR

### Description
Retrieve QR code(s) of Zalo user(s).

This API returns the QR code associated with one or multiple Zalo user IDs.  
QR codes can be used for identification, sharing contact, or other Zalo-related interactions.

---

### Method (zca-js)
api.getQR(userId)

---

### Parameters

- userId: string | string[] (optional)  
  → Zalo user ID or list of user IDs  
  → If not provided, may return QR of current account (depending on library behavior)

---

### Return
{
  [userId: string]: string; // QR code (base64 or encoded string)
}

### Example

```ts
const result = await api.getQR("user_id_here");
console.log(result);
```

